The paper proposes a deep probabilistic multi-view model that uses deep generative networks and probabilistic canonical correlation analysis (CCA) to learn shared latent representations among multiple views. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to machine learning and deep learning, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses deep generative networks to model the observations, which could also place it in sub-categories related to generative models, such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SD (Sound).
